<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Mary Steenburgen and actor Malcolm
McDowell have filed for divorce, the actress' publicist said.
   Miss Steenburgen and McDowell met while making the 1979 movie
``Time After Time.'' They have been married nine years, said Diane
Collins, a publicist for Miss Steenburgen.
   The couple had been separated for 18 months, Collins said
Wednesday. They have filed for joint custody of their children,
Lilly, 8, and Charlie, 6.
   Miss Steenburgen and McDowell said they will continue to be
``close friends.''
