<TEXT>
   Television star Michael Landon is scouting
locations around Lawrence and Baldwin for a made-for-TV movie he has
written.
   Landon, who appeared on the TV series ``Bonanza,'' ``Little House
on the Prairie'' and ``Highway to Heaven,'' said Tuesday there's
been no final decision where the NBC movie will be filmed, but he
liked the area.
   ``Everything has worked out very well here,'' he said. ``I hope
to come back.''
   Landon is scheduled to begin shooting the movie ``Where Pigeons
Go to Die'' in October. The script, an adaptation that Landon wrote
from a book by Robert Campbell, is about a grandfather, his grandson
and a pigeon.
   ``It's about people caring for each other and about loving,'' he
said. ``It's about an incident that happened to someone when they
were very small and that they'll never forget.''
   Casting has not been completed, but one thing is for sure, Landon
said: ``I'll be in it because the writer-director loves me.''
</TEXT>
