<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0570</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Bring Heavy Rain, Hail to Northern States</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms unleashed torrential rains and hail from eastern
Montana to northern Minnesota, while scattered showers also doused
parts of the Southeast and Southwest.
   Rain was continuing to fall today in several northern states.
   In Minnesota, street flooding was reported at Moose Lake, where 9
inches of rain fell in the six hours ended at 3:30 a.m. EDT.
   Several areas in North Dakota were pelted with hail the size of
golfballs, and an inch of rain fell in 15 minutes near Fargo.
   There were scattered showers and thunderstorms across southern
New Mexico Wednesday evening, and lightning caused problems with
some electrical transformers. Truth or Consequences received just
under an inch of rain.
   Scattered showers and thunderstorms also were along the southern
Atlantic Coast, and a few showers were in the Kansas City, Mo.,
area. Charleston, S.C., recorded 1\ inches of rain in the six hours
ended at 2 a.m. EDT.
   Dense fog formed this morning in parts of the Tennessee Valley.
Visibility dropped to a few hundred feet or less at Crossville, Tenn.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from the
southeastern coastal states across the Tennessee and lower Ohio
valleys, the upper Mississippi Valley and much of the northern
Plains to the northern Rockies. Winds were expected to be strong and
gusty in the northern Plains.
   Predicted highs: 80s and 90s across much of the nation; 60s and
70s along the Pacific Coast, and from the northern intermountain
region across the northern Rockies, North Dakota and the northern
Great Lakes to northern New England; near 100 degrees in parts of
Texas; and 100 to 110 in the desert Southwest.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 37 degrees at McCall,
Idaho, to 93 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Albany, N.Y. 62 fair; Atlanta 74 foggy; Boston 66 fair;
Buffalo 60 fair; Charleston, S.C. 73 cloudy; Chattanooga 72 foggy;
Cincinnati 65 fair; Cleveland 60 fair; Detroit 61 fair; Hatteras 79
fair; Jacksonville 77 fair; Key West 84 fair; Knoxville 72 foggy;
Macon 74 foggy; Miami 78 fair; New York 72 fair; Philadelphia 68
fair; Pittsburgh 62 fair; Portland, Maine 64 fair; Richmond 69 fair;
Tampa 80 fair; Washington, D.C. 73 fair.
   _Central: Birmingham 73 foggy; Bismarck 57 showery; Chicago 66
fair; Denver 70 fair; Des Moines 71 fair; Fort Worth 83 fair;
Indianapolis 65 fair; Kansas City 75 cloudy; Little Rock 76 foggy;
Louisville 73 foggy; Memphis 75 foggy; Nashville 73 foggy; New
Orleans 81 fair; North Platte 71 fair; Oklahoma City 77 fair; Omaha
73 fair; Rapid City 69 fair; St. Louis 73 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul
64 partly cloudy; Sault Ste. Marie 52 partly cloudy; San Antonio 81
fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 62 partly cloudy; Anchorage 53 partly cloudy;
Boise 53 fair; Casper 62 fair; Fairbanks 51 fair; Great Falls 51
cloudy; Honolulu 79 fair; Las Vegas 83 fair; Los Angeles 62 fair;
Medford 56 fair; Pendleton 60 fair; Phoenix 93 fair; Portland, Ore.
61 cloudy; Reno 59 fair; Salt Lake City 62 fair; San Diego 65 fair;
San Francisco 57 fair; Seattle 60 cloudy; Spokane 62 partly cloudy.
   _International: Calgary 45 partly cloudy; Montreal 55 fair;
Ottawa 57 fair; Regina 55 partly cloudy; Toronto 55 fair; Winnipeg
52 fair; Mexico City 64 cloudy; San Juan 82 fair.
