<HEAD>Window Washer Dies in High-Rise Plunge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two window washers cleaning a high-rise
building plunged 10 stories today when their platform collapsed. One
of the workers died, and two people walking near the building were
injured, police said.
   Sydney police Sgt. Doug Townsend said the platform broke free
from its fastenings above a crowded mall.
   One worker fell 132 feet to his death while the other ``rode''
the platform as it slid down a cable to the second floor, then fell
to the ground, he said.
   The condition of the surviving window washer was not immediately
known, but witnesses said he was badly cut on his face, hands and
chest.
   ``There were things strewn everywhere and people were just
distraught,'' Townsend said.
   The accident occurred while downtown Martin Place was crowded
with lunchtime shoppers. At least two people on the ground were
injured, and four children were treated for shock, police said.
