<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--DroppedTank     08-31 0170</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Dropped Tank,0175</SECOND>
<HEAD>Empty Fuel Tank Falls From Fighter Jet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>REHOBOTH BEACH, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An empty fuel tank fell off an Air
Force jet during a routine training run, crashing into a soybean
field but causing no injuries or damage, authorities said.
   The 500-pound tank, about 15 feet long and 2 feet in diameter,
dropped from an F-4 Phantom jet Wednesday afternoon about a
half-mile north of this popular beach resort, state police said.
   Capt. Walter Thorp, a Dover Air Force Base spokesman, put the
site where the 600-gallon tank fell at about 2 miles from the town.
Officials could not immediately explain the discrepancy.
   ``We heard a whistling sound, and then there was a sound like an
explosion when it hit the ground,'' said Richard Geraci, a resident
of a nearby housing development who was in his back yard when the
tank fell.
   The jet was one of three fighters that had taken off from Andrews
Air Force Base in Maryland, according to an Air Force statement.
</TEXT>
