<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Cascella     08-31 0143</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Cascella,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>Italian Painter Dies at Age 96</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILAN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Painter Michele Cascella, known for his oils
and lithographs, has died at the age of 96.
   Cascella died Tuesday at his home in Milan and was buried
Thursday in Ortona, where he was born.
   He started his career under his father, Basilio, who taught him
to use nature as a subject. He gave his first official exhibit in
Milan at the age of 15.
   Cascella took part in every edition of the Venice Biennial from
1928-42, and in 1948 he was given his own hall at the exhibit.
   He exhibited in Paris, Buenos Aires, Lausanne, Lugano, Marseille,
London, Monte Carlo and the United States.
   His works have been displayed at major museums in London,
Brussels, Los Angeles, Rome, Turin and Milan.
   He is survived by three sons and a daughter.
</TEXT>
