<HEAD>Male Nurse Accused of Having Sex With Multiple-Personality Patient</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALT LAKE CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A male nurse accused of having sex with a
patient with multiple personality disorder while she was in a child
personality faces a Sept. 21 licensing hearing before the state
Board of Nursing.
   Richard C. Heinecke of Fort Defiance, Ariz., faces two counts of
unprofessional conduct in a petition filed in October 1988 by the
state Division of Occupational and Professional Licensing.
