with a patient admitted to the psychiatric unit of a Salt Lake
Valley hospital in March 1988. Heinecke faces possible loss of his
license.
   Heinecke had sex with the woman while she was in the hospital,
took her to his home after she was discharged, then moved with her
into the home she shared with her husband, according to the
petition. The husband subsequently discovered his wife in bed with
the nurse, the division said.
