praying. Let us do the praying. Let the people who love you do the
praying.''
   Asked by reporters later whether she thought in her ``worst
fears'' her husband might suffer a mental breakdown, Mrs. Bakker
replied, ``No, I didn't. But you know, a person's mental capacity, I
suppose, can only take so much.''
   Mrs. Bakker said her husband was very distressed by the collapse
in the courtroom Wednesday of former PTL executive Steve Nelson, a
prosecution witness.
   ``I knew when I talked to Jim last night that he was in a
terrible emotional trauma and I prayed with him and we agreed that
we would trust the Lord,'' she said.
