<FIRST>u i AM-BRF--Norway-Nuclear     08-31 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Norway-Nuclear,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Protesters in Canoes Try to Block U.S. Warship in Oslo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Protesters paddled canoes into the path of
the U.S. Navy cruiser Mahan on Thursday in an attempt to keep it
from docking in Oslo harbor. The protesters claimed the Mahan had
nuclear weapons aboard.
   Norwegian tugboats circled the warship to keep 14 activists in
seven canoes at bay while the Mahan docked. Protesters from the
groups No to Atomic Weapons and the People's Movement Against War
claimed the ship was carrying seven Terrier type nuclear missiles.
   ``Our policy is to assume that vessels visiting Norwegian ports
do not carry nuclear weapons and we make the captains aware of that
assumption,'' said Arild Isegg, a Defense Ministry spokesman.
   Isegg said the U.S. cruiser and four other NATO vessels, from
Britain, Canada, West Germany and Holland, docked in Oslo following
maneuvers in the Atlantic Ocean.
   The United States does not say which warships carry nuclear
weapons.
