<FIRST>r a AM-Smith-McCall's     08-31 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Smith-McCall's,0171</SECOND>
<HEAD>Anne Mollegen Smith Named Editor In Chief of McCall's Magazine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Anne Mollegen Smith, who has held top editorial
positions at Working Woman, Redbook and Glamour magazines, was named
editor-in-chief of McCall's magazine on Thursday.
   The announcement was made by William T. Kerr, president of The
New York Times Company Magazine Group, which publishes McCall's.
   Ms. Smith, 48, last worked for Working Woman where she was editor
in chief since 1984 and directed a major redesign of the magazine.
Since 1988, she also oversaw Working Mother magazine as editorial
director for the Working Woman-McCall's Group.
   Ms. Smith served as executive editor of Glamour in 1983 and
worked for Redbook for 15 years as fiction editor, managing editor
and, from 1981 to 1983, the editor in chief. Previously, she was an
assistant editor for Ladies Home Journal.
   The Times Company acquired McCall's from Working Woman-McCall's
Group on July 27. McCall's, founded in 1876, is published monthly
and has a circulation of 5.1 million.
