<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Americans' personal incomes rose a brisk 0.7
percent in July while consumer spending also rose 0.7 percent, the
fastest growth since April, the government says.
   The Commerce Department also made significant revisions Wednesday
to previous months' figures, showing that income growth and consumer
spending were not as sluggish as previously believed.
   The growth in income, fueled by rapid growth in wages and
salaries, was the biggest monthly gain since March.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Federal disclosure rules taking effect today
will make it easier to shop for a credit card, fostering competition
that could lower interest rates for the nation's 107 million
cardholders.
   The regulations require credit card issuers to disclose the
interest rate, monthly fee, grace period and other terms in a chart
on the application used to sign up customers.
   Until now, companies have not had to disclose a card's costs
until it arrived in the mail, under federal regulations. However, a
dozen states have their own disclosure rules.
</TEXT>
