<HEAD>Dollar Up, Gold Down</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: SUBS 9th graf to change day to Thursday sted Wednesday; picks
up last graf ``Silver was ...</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar gained against major currencies in
European trading this morning.
   Gold prices were lower.
   The dollar rose sharply against the yen in Tokyo trading, gaining
1.20 yen to close at 144.28 yen. Later in London, the dollar traded
at 144.55 yen.
   It was a quiet market, with traders in Frankfurt, West Germany
saying they expected little more than end-of-the-month position
squaring while traders awaited the release of U.S. unemployment
figures on Friday. ``It's going to be dead here today,'' said one
trader.
