rates, included: 1.9586 West German marks, up from 1.9465; 1,405.75
Italian lire, up from 1,389.50; 1.6885 Swiss francs, up from 1.6770;
2.2093 Dutch guilders, up from 2.1830; 6.5970 French francs, up from
6.5515; 1.1770 Canadian dollars, up from 1.1760.
   The British pound sterling sold for $1.5715 today, cheaper than
the rate of $1.5815 late Wednesday.
   Gold opened in London at $360 a troy ounce, down 75 cents from
late Wednesday. At midmorning, the city's five major bullion dealers
fixed a recommended price of $359.60 a troy ounce.
   In Zurich, gold traded at $359.15 this morning after closing
Wednesday at $361.80.
   Earlier in Hong Kong, gold dropped $2.33 an ounce to close
Thursday at $360.04.
   Silver was quoted at $5.08 per troy ounce, down 3 cents from late
Wednesday.
