<FILEID>AP-NR-08-31-89 2035EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-AutoProdn     08-31 0144</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0151</SECOND>
<HEAD>Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
191,686 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
210,377, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago, in
which 215,327 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 121,326 cars this week,
compared with 130,980 a week ago and 136,771 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 70,542,
compared with last week's 79,397 and last year's 78,556.
   Canadian automakers were to build 19,354 cars this week, up from
15,272 a week ago and up from last year's 18,013.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 19,790, compared
with 20,107 a week ago and 18,348 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
